1.title: I am number 175 - Army Medic
1.plot: I am number 175 - Army Medic. #175 discusses shifting from Army Social Worker stateside to Army Medic in Vietnam in what he calls the ultimate OJT (on job training). Men born September 13 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 175.

2.title: I am number 030 - Army Cook
2.plot: I Am Number 030 - Army Cook. #030 recounts his feelings upon learning he was being made an Army Cook and subsequently his assignment to the Central Highland's of Vietnam in the mid 1960's. Men born March 31 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 030.

3.title: I am number 141 - Army Radio Operator
3.plot: I Am Number 141 - Army Radio Operator. #141 was stationed outside Saigon and talks about the availability of drugs and prostitutes. Men born August 18 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 141.

4.title: I am number 200 - Air Force - Medical Draft
4.plot: I Am Number 200 - Air Force Medical Draft. #200 talks about the lesser known Doctor Draft, the Berry Plan, and finding his passion for Endocrinology. Men Born March 19 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 200.

5.title: I am number 113 - Civilian
5.plot: I Am Number 113 - Civilian. #113 shares how his status was changed from a II S (Activity in Study) to a I A (Available for Military Service) and eventually to a IV F (Not qualified for any Military Service). Men Born September 15 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 113.

6.title: I am number 128 - Air Force Personnel
6.plot: I Am Number 128 - Air Force Personnel. #128 reminisces about McGuire Air Force Base and recalls his arrival at Tan Son Nhut Air Base in Vietnam when they changed to the series 681 Military Payment Certificates. Men Born December 18 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 128.

7.title: I am number 353 - Civilian
7.plot: I Am Number 353 - Civilian. #353 remembers sitting in the drivers seat of his '67 Chevy and reading the results of the August 5, 1971 lottery for the 1972 draft. Men Born February 16, 1952 were assigned Lottery Draft Number 353.

8.title: I am number 335 - Air Force Aircraft Loadmaster
8.plot: I Am Number 335 - Air Force Aircraft Loadmaster. #335 describes fulfilling a life long dream of Flying; and his return to Vietnam in 1997 to repatriate MIA remains. Men Born June 9 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 335.

9.title: I am number 320 - Civillian
9.plot: I Am Number 320 - Civilian. #320 conveys his passion for music and the power it has to bring people together. Men Born December 15 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 320.

10.title: I am number 277 - Army Staff Sergeant
10.plot: I Am Number 277 - Army Staff Sergeant. #277 candidly discusses hazing like practices in boot camp as a necessity to prepare troops for combat. Men Born July 9 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 277.

11.title: I am number 173 - Civilian
11.plot: I Am Number 173 - Civilian. #173 recalls his time studying at New York University and the 1970 lockouts on campus. Men Born December 26 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 173.

12.title: I am number 224 - Army Radio Operator
12.plot: I Am Number 224 - Army Radio Operator. 224 talks about bonding with his Colonel when asked to bar tend for his officers during their late night planning meetings out in the field. Men Born January 6 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 224.

13.title: I am number 181 - ARNG Armor Recon Scout
13.plot: I Am Number 181 - Army National Guard - Armor Recon Scout. #181 talks about boot camp and the friends he made. Men born February 8 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 181.

14.title: I am number 094 - Navy Radarman.
14.plot: I Am Number 094 - Navy Radarman. #094 leaves for a WestPac Cruise aboard the USS Wallace L Lind, DD-703. Men Born October 28 (1944-1950) were assigned Lottery Draft Number 094.
